#program

  %h2 Attendees levels and suggested paths
  %p
    These path suggestions are for your information only.
    %br/
    This is one of the many ways to organise your day, with no obligation to follow particular sessions.
  %p
    You can choose your sessions as you go too.
    %br/
    Having discussions with participants,
    speakers and organisers during the breaks can help you identify the subjects you might be interested in.
  %p
    Let yourself be open to your agenda changes and surprises !

  %h3 Beginner-friendly path
  %p Beginner-friendly  workshops and talks are labeled with #{label :beginner}
  %p
    If you are new to Agile, we recommend you to choose between sessions marked as beginner-friendly.
    %br/
    Sessions marked with this label don't require any special prerequisites in order to be understood and fully enjoyed.


  %h3 Practitioner's path
  %p Practitioner's workshops and talks are labeled with #{label :practitioner}
  %p The talks and workshops in this session are targeted for people who are familiar with agile methods and approaches.

  %h3 Expert's path
  %p Experts workshops and talks are labeled with #{label :expert}
  %p In these talks and workshops, the basics won't be explained. The presenter assumes that you are well-versed in agile and will present advanced topics.

  %h2 Session types
  %p During the conference 2 type of sessions are proposed:
  %ul
    %li Talks : Presenter is speaking for most of the time (often from a slide deck), with audience interaction. <br /> They are marked with: #{ label :talk }
    %li Workshops : Primarily focused on hands-on participation with the audience. <br /> They are marked with: #{ label :workshop }

  %br/


